Hmm, okay, upon closer inspection, you are right. The problem I have is that I have the following definition in my .cshrc file:<p><pre><code>    alias precmd &#x27;echo `date` &quot;#@#&quot; `pwd` &quot;#@#&quot; `history 1` >> ~/.complete_history&#x27;
</code></pre>
This basically saves all my commands to a file (which is very handy, by the way).<p>So somehow this interferes with the curly braces. I put the history part in double-quotes, and now it works:<p><pre><code>    alias precmd &#x27;echo `date` &quot;#@#&quot; `pwd` &quot;#@#&quot; &quot;`history 1`&quot; >> ~/.complete_history&#x27;
</code></pre>
Thanks for helping me solve this :)
